         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>SME Holding Fund – procurement of Fund Managers (Delivery Agents)</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>383404</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="79412000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The SME Holding Fund is a Fund-of-Funds managed by Scottish Government which invests in microfinance, debt and early stage equity funds which further invest in Small and Medium-sized Enterprises (see European Commission definition at: http://ec.europa.eu/growth/smes/business-friendly-environment/sme-definition_en) with growth and/or export potential. The SME Holding Fund is part-financed by the European Regional Development Fund from the 2014-2020 European Structural Funds Programmes in Scotland.</P>
               <P>There will be an Open Day for this requirement on 11.4.2018, the details of which are included below and the invitation form is included within additional documents as part of this PIN Notice.</P>
               <P>Please contact Paul Packett at paul.packett@gov.scot by 4.4.2018 should you wish to attend.</P>
               <P>Open Day is booked for 11.4.2018, 12:30-15:00 at:</P>
               <P>Scottish Government, 5 Atlantic Quay, 150 Broomielaw, Glasgow, G2 8LU.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Microfinance</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>1</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="66171000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKM"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>We intend to appoint envisage one delivery agent in the microfinance lot, managing a microfinance fund on our behalf lending up to 25 000 to businesses employing less than 10 staff.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="2">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Equity</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>3</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="66171000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKM"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>We intend to appoint 2 delivery agents in the equity lot who will manage funds which provide equity finance to SMEs with high growth potential, investing equity finance in amounts of up to 2 000 000 and within a maximum deal ceiling of 10 000 000.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="3">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Debt</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>2</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="66171000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKM"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>We intend to appoint 2 delivery agents in the debt lot, one managing a fund which provides loans in the range 25 000 GBP — 100 000 GBP to SMEs and the other managing a fund which provides loans in the range 100 000 to 1 000 000 GBP to SMEs.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-07-02</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>The Scottish Government, under the SME Holding Fund, intends to procure a small number of Fund Managers (Delivery Agents) who will manage on its behalf: microfinance funds providing loans of up to 25 000 GBP); debt funds providing loans to SMEs in the ranges 25 000 GBP — 100 000 GBP and 100 000 GBP — 1 000 000 GBP; and early stage equity funds providing equity investment of up to 2 000 000 GBP per SME within a deal ceiling of 10 000 000 GBP. Scottish Government will fully finance the capital costs of such funds, and will also pay a management fee to successful bidders. Fee levels are not capped but will be determined by a “best value for money” assessment as part of the bidding process. Realisations from each of the funds managed by successful bidders will accrue to Scottish Government, specifically the SME Holding Fund. Scottish Government will allocate 75 000 000 GBP — 105 000 000 GBP to successful bidders who will then invest their respective funds over a 3 year period from 8.2018, followed by a portfolio management period. There is the possibility of additional funds becoming available over a longer investment period (up to 12.2023), subject to performance.</P>
               <P>Please contact Pat McHugh at pat.mchugh@gov.scot should you wish to discuss the service provision further.</P>
               <P>Note: To register your interest in this notice and obtain any additional information please visit the Public Contracts Scotland Web Site at http://www.publiccontractsscotland.gov.uk/Search/Search_Switch.aspx?ID=529456</P>
               <P>(SC Ref:529456).</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-02-13</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
         </COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
